This paper is about feature selection in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper deals with learning non-linear feature maps. Other likely categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these sub-categories are also relevant to feature selection and machine learning.
